    <div class="body">
        <p>Hello,</p>

<p>Apologies if this is not a bug but my mistake:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$date = new Zend_Date();
echo $date-&gt;getYear();
//date_default_timezone_set('Europe/Berlin')
//resources.locale.default = "de_DE"
</code></pre>

<p>gets me:</p>

<pre class="literal">
01.01.2010 01:00:00
</pre>

<p>only:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$date = new Zend_Date();
$date-&gt;setTimezone('Europe/London');
echo $date-&gt;getYear()
</code></pre>

<p>gets me the correct hour:</p>

<pre class="literal">
01.01.2010 00:00:00
</pre>

<p>Also, an explicit</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$loc = new Zend_Locale();
$loc-&gt;setLocale('de_DE');
$date = new Zend_Date();
$date-&gt;setTimezone('Europe/Berlin');
echo $date-&gt;getYear();
</code></pre>

<p>makes it an hour later :(</p>

<p>Is this a bug?</p>

